(8, 1, 'rule', 'General Rules & Regulations', '', '', 10, 'English', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Event organizers&#39;&nbsp;decision will be final and binding.</li>\r\n	<li>Rules are subject to change as per the discretion of the event organizers. The department coordinators will be informed about any such changes made after the release of the rulebook.</li>\r\n	<li>Organizers are not responsible for damage or loss of personal property.</li>\r\n	<li>For all the events, the decision of the judges is final and any arguments in this regard will not be entertained.</li>\r\n	<li>No departments are permitted to use the Barn Hall after March 1st unless allotted slots by the organizers. Departments will be disqualified if found to do so.</li>\r\n	<li>Unruly behaviour or use of obscene language will invite reduction in overall points tally of the department and/or immediate disqualification of the participant/team/department, as is found appropriate.</li>\r\n	<li>In case of tie between two teams (for all events) For first place: there will be no 2nd place and the points of the first and 2nd place will be added and split equally among the teams.<br />\r\n	For 2nd place: There will be no 3rd place and the points of the 2nd and 3rd place will be added and split equally among the teams.<br />\r\n	For third place: the points will be divided equally.</li>\r\n	<li>Time limit, number of entries per event and submission deadlines must be strictly adhered to for all the events. Delayed submissions will not be accepted.</li>\r\n	<li>A hardcopy&nbsp;of the rule book will be available with the Department coordinators</li>\r\n	<li>Event Managers are not allowed to take part in their respective events.</li>\r\n	<li>Except for DOMS and MCA, only B.Tech students of 2nd, 3rd and 4th years (and 1st, 5th years too in case of Architecture) &amp; M.Techs 1st and 2nd yrs&nbsp;are allowed to participate as part of their respective departments.</li>\r\n	<li>With regard to all stage events, the time provided to &quot;clear the stage&quot;&nbsp;includes the time for vacating the backstage and leaving the Barn through the back exit.</li>\r\n	<li>All time deadlines for submission will be in accordance with http://www.worldtimeserver.com/current_time_in_IN.aspx</li>\r\n	<li>For all events involving in-person submission, one of the event coordinators will be available at Sun Lab from half an hour before the submission deadline. Participants are however required to confirm with the respective head in this regard. The organizers will NOT be responsible for unexpected changes in venue in this regard.</li>\r\n	<li>The participants are requested NOT to make any assumptions that have not been stated clearly in the rulebook. The organizers will NOT be held responsible for any confusion arriving due to the same. Please get such issues clarified from the organizers beforehand.</li>\r\n	<li>For issues regarding any of the events, feel free to contact the respective heads, whose contacts have been included subsequently.</li>\r\n	<li>STUDENT ACTIVITY CENTRE AND BARN HALL ARE STRICTLY PROHIBITED FOR THE USAGE BY ALL DEPARTMENTS FROM 27TH FEBRUARY, 2013 EXCEPT DURING THE ALLOTED SLOTS BY THE NITTFEST&rsquo;13 ORGANISING TEAM.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n'),
(121, 2, 'main-quiz', 'Main Quiz', '', '7;5;3', 0, 'English', ''),
(122, 2, 'lone-wolf', 'Lone Wolf', '', '5;3;2', 1, 'English', '<p>Now this is what you&rsquo;d want to be looking forward to. Or maybe not so much so. If you think you&nbsp;<span style="line-height: 1.6em;">know it all, we really, really want to know if you do. Try getting yourself tested, or possibly get to&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">know what you didn&rsquo;t.</span></p>\r\n'),
(123, 2, 'jam', 'JAM', '', '5;3;2', 2, 'English', '<p><b>AROUND THE WORLD IN 60 SECONDS!!</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you keep talking nonstop,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>think you&rsquo;re funny (when you&rsquo;re actually being annoying), interrupt</p>\r\n\r\n<p>people while they&rsquo;re talking and are a Grammar Nazi, JAM is probably for you. Just don&rsquo;t do these</p>\r\n\r\n<p>to the moderator though, you could end up getting banned. Or worse.</p>\r\n'),
(124, 2, 'crossie', 'Crossie', '', '5;3;2', 3, 'English', '<p><strong>Get the word right....win your way through black and white!!</strong></p>\r\n'),
(125, 2, 'debate', 'Debate', '', '6;4;2', 4, 'English', '<p><strong>Arguably the Best!!!</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The ultimate platform for the argumentative NITTian. Stick to your stance , hold your ground or&nbsp;<span style="line-height: 1.6em;">go down defending it. Wage a war of words in the Asians style. Try to break down the&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">opposition&rsquo;s argument while you make your own.</span></p>\r\n'),
(126, 2, 'puzzle-champ', 'Puzzle Champ', '', '7;5;3', 5, 'English', '<p><strong>Piece it together!!</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:.4in;">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Will you be able to prove that you really have all gears working up there? Solve a tough</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:.4in;">&nbsp;&nbsp; challenge, finish a sequence, complete the picture, maybe not literally in any such sense, but</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:.4in;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; just go ahead and flaunt your strength where it actually mattersyour</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:.4in;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; brain. What&rsquo;s it that you&rsquo;ll</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:.4in;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; have to be doing? That&rsquo;s a puzzle too. But one thing you will be doing is getting your logical</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left:.4in;">&nbsp;&nbsp; thinking in full flow as you try solving the barrage of puzzles that come your way.</p>\r\n'),
(127, 2, 'good-word', 'Whatâ€™s the Good Word?', '', '5;3;2', 6, 'English', '<p>There may be a lot of good words, but THE good word is the only one that&rsquo;ll help you with the&nbsp;<span style="line-height: 1.6em;">clues here. You probably won&rsquo;t understand a lot of clues in this event, but that&rsquo;s okay, neither do&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">we.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>What&rsquo;s The Good Word (or WTGW for short) is a mashup of a number of word games. There&nbsp;<span style="line-height: 1.6em;">are no requirements for a WTGW specialist. Some may tell you you need to be good with the&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">language and good with puzzles, but we can assure you that specialists here are neither</span></p>\r\n'),
(128, 2, 'pixie', 'Pixie', '', '7;5;3', 7, 'English', '<p><strong>a.k.a. PICTIONARY&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>One person guesses what the other draws and vice versa. You don&rsquo;t need to be an artist to play</p>\r\n\r\n<p>pictionary, just have an understanding with your team mate. Come well equipped with enough</p>\r\n\r\n<p>general knowledge and SpEnt trivia to get through varied topics ranging from the bombing of</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hiroshima to Ozzy Osbourne biting off bats&rsquo; heads.</p>\r\n'),
(129, 2, 'dumb-c', 'Dumb - C', '', '7;5;3', 8, 'English', '<p>MIME.GUESS.SIMPLE? NOT QUITE.</p>\r\n'),
(130, 2, 'scrabble', 'Scrabble', '', '5;3;2', 9, 'English', '<p><strong>MAKE YOUR HITS MULTIPLY LIKE&nbsp;RABBITS!!</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Classic game of scrabble; nothing more to explain. The words go up, down, left and right. Show</p>\r\n\r\n<p>off your knowledge of the Queen&rsquo;s English, but remember bigger words aren&rsquo;t always better!</p>\r\n'),
(131, 2, 'pot-pourri', 'Pot - Pourri', '', '8;6;4', 10, 'English', '<p><b>THE JACK OF ALL TRADES !</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A mixed bag of events to test everyone&rsquo;s versatility. Miming, Number games or Word Games.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the few places where the Jack of all arts probably beats the Master of any one. Come</p>\r\n\r\n<p>prepared because you never know what&rsquo;s going to hit you. Its a mixed bag!</p>\r\n'),
(132, 2, 'spelling-bee', 'Spelling Bee', '', '3;2;1', 11, 'English', ''),
(133, 2, 'spent-quiz', 'Spent Quiz', '', '7;5;3', 12, 'English', '<p>Here&rsquo;s your chance to flaunt knowledge gained by years of experience sitting in front of the idiot box. From Stephanie Seymour to Stephanie Rice, be ready to be quizzed on the interesting, ugly, weird or in this case beautiful from the world of Sports and Entertainment.</p>\r\n'),
(134, 121, 'general-information', 'General Information', '', '', 0, 'English', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>General Quiz.</li>\r\n	<li>Written prelims.</li>\r\n	<li>Finals for 6-8 qualifying teams.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Registration:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>On the spot.</li>\r\n	<li>Any number of teams per department.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Prelims (written):</strong><br />\r\n1. Three members per team.<br />\r\n2. The top 6-8 teams with the highest scores go through to the finals</p>\r\n'),
(135, 122, 'general-information', 'General Information', '', '', 0, 'English', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Registration:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>On the spot</li>\r\n	<li>Maximum number of participants per department is unlimited.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Prelims:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Participants are short listed for the finals from the preliminary round.</li>\r\n	<li>6-8 will qualify to the finals.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n'),
(136, 123, 'general-information', 'General Information', '', '', 0, 'English', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Registration:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>On the spot</li>\r\n	<li>Maximum number of participants per department is unlimited.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Prelims:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Participants are short listed for the finals through a series of preliminary rounds</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n'),
(137, 124, 'general-information', 'General Information', '', '', 0, 'English', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The usual cryptic crossword solving.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Registration:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>On the spot during NITTFEST&rsquo;13</li>\r\n	<li>Any number of teams per department</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Prelims:</strong><br />\r\n1. Two members per team.<br />\r\n2. Maximum time allotted -- 45 minutes.<br />\r\n3. The first 6-8&nbsp;teams with the highest scores go through to the finals.<br />\r\nThe format and rules for the finals will be announced on the spot</p>\r\n'),
(138, 125, 'general-information', 'General Information', '', '', 0, 'English', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Two members per team.</li>\r\n	<li>The maximum number of teams per department in prelims is 2.</li>\r\n	<li>Preliminary rounds, followed by subsequent rounds where 2 teams go head to head. The details will be notified later</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n'),
(139, 126, 'general-information', 'General Information', '', '', 0, 'English', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Participants are expected to solve a collection of puzzles that require an ability to play with words, alphabets and more.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Prelims(written):</strong><br />\r\n1. Three members per team.<br />\r\n2. Maximum time allotted -- 45 minutes.<br />\r\n3. The first eight teams with the highest scores go through to the finals.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Finals:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rules will be announced on the spot.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Registration:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the spot Any number of teams per department</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Format:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Written prelims followed by an on-stage finals for 6-8 qualifying teams.</p>\r\n'),
(140, 127, 'general-information', 'General Information', '', '', 0, 'English', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Written prelims.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Registration:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>On the spot</li>\r\n	<li>Any number of teams per department</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Prelims(written):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Two&nbsp;members per team.<br />\r\n2. Maximum time allotted -- 45 minutes.<br />\r\n3. The first six or eight teams with the highest scores go through to the finals.</p>\r\n'),
(141, 128, 'general-information', 'General Information', '', '', 0, 'English', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Draw. Guess.</li>\r\n	<li>Team Size: 3</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Format:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Split prelims followed by finals for 6-8 qualifying teams.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Registration:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>On the spot</li>\r\n	<li>Any number of teams per department</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Prelims (written):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Three members per team. Standard pixie rules. Any deviations will be mentioned.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Finals:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Rules will be announced on the spot.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n'),
(142, 129, 'general-information', 'General Information', '', '', 0, 'English', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Mime. Guess</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Format:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Prelims followed by finals for 6 qualifying teams.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Registration:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>On the spot</li>\r\n	<li>3 teams per department.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Prelims(written):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Three members per team. Standard dumb-c rules.</li>\r\n	<li>Any deviations&nbsp;will be mentioned.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Finals:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Rules will be announced on the spot</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n'),
(143, 130, 'general-information', 'General Information', '', '', 0, 'English', '<p><strong>Registrations:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>On the spot.</li>\r\n	<li>Any number of teams per department in prelims.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Prelims(written):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Two members per team.<br />\r\n2. Maximum time allotted -- 45 minutes.<br />\r\n3. The first six or eight teams with the highest scores go through to the finals.<br />\r\n4. A screen shot of the game is shown and the participants have to make words.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Finals</strong>&nbsp;is more or less the same.</p>\r\n'),
(144, 131, 'general-information', 'General Information', '', '', 0, 'English', '<p><strong>Registration:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>On the spot.</li>\r\n	<li>2 teams per department.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Prelims(written):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>5 members per team.One person per year AND maximum of three members from a single year.</li>\r\n	<li>Prelims will be split&nbsp;prelims. The scores are added up.</li>\r\n	<li>The first eight teams with the highest scores go through to the finals.</li>\r\n	<li>Only two teams per department is allowed to register.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Finals:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. The competition consists of 6 rounds.<br />\r\n2. The format will be announced during the event to maintain the element of surprise.</p>\r\n'),
(145, 132, 'general-information', 'General Information', '', '', 0, 'English', '<p><strong>Registration:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>On the spot.</li>\r\n	<li>Maximum of 8 participants per department.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Prelims(written):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. This is a solo event.<br />\r\n2. The first 6-8 participants with the highest scores go through to the finals, subject to a maximum of 2 per department.</p>\r\n'),
(146, 133, 'general-information', 'General Information', '', '', 0, 'English', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Written prelims.</li>\r\n	<li>Finals for 6-8 qualifying teams.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Registration:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>On the spot.</li>\r\n	<li>Any number of teams per department.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Prelims (written):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Three members per team.<br />\r\n2. Maximum time allotted &ndash; 30-45 minutes.<br />\r\n3. The top 6-8 teams&nbsp;with the highest scores go through to the finals.</p>\r\n'),
(147, 5, 'dominoes', 'Dominoes', '', '8;5;3', 0, 'English', '<p>let the fall begin!!!<br />\r\nHow one small thing can set off a huge chain of events!!......one dominoe it strikes perfectly and u score!!</p>\r\n'),
